TY  - JOUR
AU  - Gao, Janet
AU  - Wang, Wenyu
AU  - Wu, Yufeng
T1  - Human Capital Portability and Careers in Finance
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhae033
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 37
IS  - 9
SP  - 2732
EP  - 2778
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - How does firm-specific human capital shape careers in the finance industry? We build a dynamic model where workers accumulate portable and nonportable (firm-specific) human capital and learn about their match quality with employers. Estimating the model using granular data on M&amp;A advisory bankers, we show that a large fraction of bankers’ human capital is nonportable, ranging from 12% to 46% across different firm types. Bankers make a dynamic trade-off between portability and returns on human capital, leading to time-varying job preferences over their life cycle. Our results have broad implications for careers in finance and the provision of financial services.
Y2  - 10/27/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhae033
ER  - 



